<REFENTRY id="find">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
find
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>find</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
search for files in a directory hierarchy
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>find</COMMAND> shall behave as specified in 
<XREF LINKEND=STD.SUSv3>, except as
described below.
</PARA>

</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Differences</TITLE>
<REFSECT2>
<TITLE>Pattern Matching</TITLE
<para>
Some elements of the Pattern Matching Notation are optional;
see <xref linkend="localization-glob">.
</para>
</REFSECT2>
<REFSECT2>
<TITLE>Option and Operand Handling</TITLE>
<PARA>
Options and operands to <command>find</command> shall behave
as described in 
<xref linkend="STD.SUSv3">, except as follows:
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><parameter>-H</parameter></term>
<listitem><para>need not be supported</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><parameter>-L</parameter></term>
<listitem><para>need not be supported</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><parameter>-exec ... +</parameter></term>
<listitem><para>argument aggregation need not be supported</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
<NOTE><TITLE>Rationale</TITLE>
<para>The <parameter>-H</parameter> and <parameter>-L</parameter> options
are only supported in the most recent versions of <command>find</command>,
as is argument aggregation. When this version of <command>find</command>
becomes widely adopted, these limitations will be removed.
</para>
</NOTE>
</para>
</REFSECT2>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
